Linus Oota, Lafia The governorship candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Nasarawa State, Engr Abdullahi Sule, has expressed optimism that he will win the governorship election in the state with a wide margin. He stated this shortly after casting his vote at exactly 10 am in his village in Gudi. He said that APC has no reason to lose the governorship election after sweeping all the National Assembly seats in the last election and delivering the state to President Muhammadu Buhari. He explained that the achievements of the outgoing governor was the reason for the massive votes APC garnered in the state.   Click Here>>>>>>Anti-kidnap and anti-theft device for tracking and listening<<<<<< 